  <h2 class="tw-text-2xl tw-font-bold tw-text-gray-900">About Ayah Topics</h2>

  <p>
    The Ayah Topics resource provides three types of classifications for each verse (ayah) in the Qur'an: 
    <strong>Ontology</strong> (conceptual relationships from Quranic Arabic Corpus), 
    <strong>Thematic</strong> (themes based on Clear Quran), and 
    <strong>General</strong> (broader categorizations). 
    This multi-dimensional resource helps you understand the subjects, concepts, and themes discussed in specific 
    verses from different perspectives, enabling deeper study and comprehensive cross-referencing of related 
    content throughout the Qur'an.
  </p>

  <h3 class="tw-text-xl tw-font-semibold tw-text-gray-900">Topic Types</h3>
  
  <div class="tw-space-y-4">
    <div class="tw-bg-blue-50 tw-border-l-4 tw-border-blue-500 tw-p-4">
      <h4 class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-blue-900 tw-mb-3">1. Ontology Topics</h4>
      <p class="tw-mb-3">
        <strong>Definition:</strong> Ayahs that describe the nature of existence and entities in the unseen 
        or seen world. They focus on <em>what exists</em> and its attributes.
      </p>
      <div class="tw-bg-white tw-p-3 tw-rounded tw-border tw-border-blue-200">
        <p class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-sm tw-mb-2">Example:</p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-mb-2 qpc-hafs tw-text-right">
          "اللَّهُ لَا إِلَٰهَ إِلَّا هُوَ الْحَيُّ الْقَيُّومُ"
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-italic tw-mb-1">
          "Allah – there is no deity except Him, the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of [all] existence." (Qur'an 2:255)
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-text-gray-700">
          → Speaks about God's existence and attributes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tw-bg-green-50 tw-border-l-4 tw-border-green-500 tw-p-4">
      <h4 class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-green-900 tw-mb-3">2. Thematic Topics</h4>
      <p class="tw-mb-3">
        <strong>Definition:</strong> Ayahs that revolve around recurring themes or subjects conveying 
        guidance, morality, or lessons. They are concept-based rather than existence-based. Primarily 
        based on the Clear Quran translation.
      </p>
      <div class="tw-bg-white tw-p-3 tw-rounded tw-border tw-border-green-200">
        <p class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-sm tw-mb-2">Example:</p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-mb-2 qpc-hafs tw-text-right">
          "وَأَقِيمُوا الصَّلَاةَ وَآتُوا الزَّكَاةَ وَارْكَعُوا مَعَ الرَّاكِعِينَ"
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-italic tw-mb-1">
          "Establish prayer and give zakah and bow with those who bow [in worship]." (Qur'an 2:43)
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-text-gray-700">
          → Theme of worship and religious duty.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tw-bg-purple-50 tw-border-l-4 tw-border-purple-500 tw-p-4">
      <h4 class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-purple-900 tw-mb-3">3. General Topics</h4>
      <p class="tw-mb-3">
        <strong>Definition:</strong> Ayahs that address broad, multi-purpose guidance without being confined 
        to ontology or a single theme. They combine stories, laws, morals, and reminders in a comprehensive way.
      </p>
      <div class="tw-bg-white tw-p-3 tw-rounded tw-border tw-border-purple-200">
        <p class="tw-font-semibold tw-text-sm tw-mb-2">Example:</p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-mb-2 qpc-hafs tw-text-right">
          "إِنَّ اللَّهَ يَأْمُرُ بِالْعَدْلِ وَالْإِحْسَانِ وَإِيتَاءِ ذِي الْقُرْبَىٰ وَيَنْهَىٰ عَنِ الْفَحْشَاءِ وَالْمُنكَرِ"
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-italic tw-mb-1">
          "Indeed, Allah commands justice and good conduct and giving to relatives and forbids immorality 
          and oppression." (Qur'an 16:90)
        </p>
        <p class="tw-text-sm tw-text-gray-700">
          → Covers ethics, law, and social order in one ayah.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 class="tw-text-xl tw-font-semibold tw-text-gray-900">Understanding the Data</h3>

  <p>
    Each verse can be associated with multiple topics across all three categories: ontological, thematic, and general. 
    The topics are organized hierarchically, meaning each topic may have parent topics (broader categories) and child 
    topics (more specific subcategories). This multi-dimensional classification system allows for comprehensive 
    understanding of each verse from different perspectives.
  </p>

  <h3 class="tw-text-xl tw-font-semibold tw-text-gray-900">Database Structure</h3>

  <p>The QUL exports ayah topics data as a SQLite database with the following structure:</p>

  <ul class="tw-list-disc tw-pl-6 tw-space-y-2">
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">topic_id</code>: 
      Unique identifier for the topic
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">topic_name</code>: 
      The English name of the topic
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">arabic_name</code>: 
      The Arabic name or transliteration of the topic (if available)
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">verse_key</code>: 
      The verse identifier in format "chapter:verse" (e.g., "2:255")
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">is_ontology</code>: 
      Boolean indicating if this is an ontology topic
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">is_thematic</code>: 
      Boolean indicating if this is a thematic topic
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">parent_topic_id</code>: 
      ID of the parent topic (for hierarchical organization)
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-2 tw-py-1 tw-rounded">description</code>: 
      Detailed description of what the topic encompasses
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="tw-text-xl tw-font-semibold tw-text-gray-900">Use Cases</h3>

  <ul class="tw-list-disc tw-pl-6 tw-space-y-2">
    <li>Study verses related to specific Islamic concepts or themes</li>
    <li>Create topic-based study guides and educational materials</li>
    <li>Build search and discovery features for Qur'anic applications</li>
    <li>Enable cross-referencing of related verses across the Qur'an</li>
    <li>Develop thematic tafsir and commentary tools</li>
    <li>Support academic research on Qur'anic themes and concepts</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="tw-text-xl tw-font-semibold tw-text-gray-900">Navigation Tips</h3>

  <ul class="tw-list-disc tw-pl-6 tw-space-y-2">
    <li>Browse the topics list to see all available topics with pagination</li>
    <li>Click on any topic to see all ayahs associated with it</li>
    <li>Topics are color-coded: blue for ontology, green for thematic, purple for general</li>
    <li>In the topic detail page, highlighted words (in green) show specific words relevant to that topic</li>
    <li>Use the "Back to Topics List" link to return to the main list</li>
  </ul>

